===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Stinson Beach had a population of 541. The population density was {{convert|606.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Stinson Beach was 463 (85.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 3 (0.6%) [[African Americans|African American]], 3 (0.6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 13 (2.4%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 15 (2.8%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 43 (7.9%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 29 persons (5.4%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Stinson Beach CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0674172 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 535 people (98.9% of the population) lived in households, 6 (1.1%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and no one was institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 290 households, out of which 31 (10.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 116 (40.0%) were married-couple households, 18 (6.2%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 97 (33.4%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 59 (20.3%) had a male householder with no partner present. 124 households (42.8%) were one person, and 76 (26.2%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.84.<ref name=DP1/> There were 146 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (50.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Stinson Beach CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0674172 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 36 people (6.7%) under the age of 18, 27 people (5.0%) aged 18 to 24, 92 people (17.0%) aged 25 to 44, 162 people (29.9%) aged 45 to 64, and 224 people (41.4%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 60.4{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 89.2 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 751 housing units at an average density of {{convert|841.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 290 (38.6%) were occupied. Of these, 195 (67.2%) were owner-occupied, and 95 (32.8%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0674172|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715033410/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0674172|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Stinson Beach CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Stinson Beach had a population of 632. The population density was {{convert|433.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Stinson Beach was 582 (92.1%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 3 (0.5%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 8 (1.3%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 14 (2.2%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 1 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 9 (1.4%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 15 (2.4%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 33 persons (5.2%).

The Census reported that 629 people (99.5% of the population) lived in households, 3 (0.5%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 339 households, out of which 50 (14.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 134 (39.5%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 14 (4.1%) had a female householder with no husband present, 10 (2.9%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 26 (7.7%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 8 (2.4%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 147 households (43.4%) were made up of individuals, and 45 (13.3%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 1.86.  There were 158 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (46.6% of all households); the average family size was 2.54.

The population was spread out, with 76 people (12.0%) under the age of 18, 26 people (4.1%) aged 18 to 24, 117 people (18.5%) aged 25 to 44, 278 people (44.0%) aged 45 to 64, and 135 people (21.4%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 54.4 years. For every 100 females, there were 94.5 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 95.1 males.

There were 773 housing units at an average density of {{convert|529.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 209 (61.7%) were owner-occupied, and 130 (38.3%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 2.3%; the rental vacancy rate was 9.7%.  425 people (67.2% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 204 people (32.3%) lived in rental housing units.
===2000===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=2008-01-31 |title=Measuring America's People and Economy|website=U.S. Census}}</ref> of 2000, the median income for a household in the CDP was $87,679, and the median income for a family was $105,827. Males had a median income of $58,750 versus $56,875 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $62,452.  About 3.8% of families and 5.1% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 11.8% of those under the age of eighteen and 10.4% of those 65 or over.

